sentences.english: The tops of the beggar's shoes had worn so thin that his toes were poking through.
sentences.chinese: 叫化子的鞋幫磨得很薄，腳趾頭快要出來了。

sentences.english: When that lawn mower cuts off your toes, don't come running to me.
sentences.chinese: 當割草機切下你的腳趾頭的時候，你別跑來找我。

sentences.english: One can forget one' s love for a period even over a stubbed toe.
sentences.chinese: 就連一隻撞傷的腳趾頭也能讓人把愛情暫放一邊。

sentences.english: Someone tramped on my toes on the bus .
sentences.chinese: 有人在公共汽車上踩了我的腳趾頭。

sentences.english: he could feel her toes dig into the carpet .
sentences.chinese: 他可以感到她的腳趾頭深深地跨進地毯裏。

sentences.english: Why is the muscle of beetle-crusher foot head painful?
sentences.chinese: 爲什麼大腳趾頭的筋會痛？

sentences.english: Employee got his toe caught in a vent cover.
sentences.chinese: 被通氣孔的蓋子卡傷了腳趾頭。

sentences.english: We wiggled our toes in the cool water of the creek.
sentences.chinese: 我們在小溪冰涼的水中扭動我們的腳趾頭。

sentences.english: When toe head plays basketball, contused how to do?
sentences.chinese: 腳趾頭打籃球的時候挫傷了怎麼辦？

sentences.english: The son takes off his shoes and wiggles his toes in the grass.
sentences.chinese: 兒子脫了鞋，在草叢裏擺弄腳趾頭。
你踩在我的腳趾頭上了。

sentences.english: And boy does my toe hurt when I put my boots on.
sentences.chinese: 在穿上靴子時，腳趾頭也痛。

sentences.english: His thoughts went to his boot, to the mushrooms in the toe.
sentences.chinese: 他的思緒回到了他的靴子上，那些腳趾頭處的蘑菇。

sentences.english: Interdigital, or toe web infection, is the most common kind of athlete's foot.
sentences.chinese: 趾間或腳趾頭的感染，是腳癬中最常見的。

sentences.english: Stand back! You're stepping on my toes.
sentences.chinese: 向後站!你踩在我的腳趾頭上了。
